# UI Design Rules

## MUST
- Follow `docs/rules/ui-rules.md`.
- Use light theme only.
- Keep UI dense, calm, and financial-tool oriented.
- Prioritize information scanning over decoration.
- Use clear borders, neutral backgrounds, compact spacing, and small status colors.
- User-facing web should follow a Perplexity-like calm research UI: warm off-white background, soft beige panels, low-contrast borders, dark ink text, and teal accents.
- User-facing web tokens: page `#FCFCF9`, panel `#F7F5EE`, card `#FFFFFF`, border `#D9D5C9`, primary text `#102A2C`, secondary text `#5F6868`, accent `#20808D`, accent hover `#186A73`.
- Admin may keep the existing neutral light workspace tokens for table density and operational clarity.
- Mobile layout must be single-column with no horizontal scroll.
- Desktop Home uses sidebar, feed, and market panel.
- Admin uses sidebar plus table/config workspace.

## FORBIDDEN
- No dark backgrounds as primary UI.
- No dark sidebar, header, or cards.
- No neon crypto styling.
- No large gradients or marketing hero layouts for product screens.
- No nested cards or overflowing text.
- No Narrative item in mobile bottom navigation.
